parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, compromising the safety of the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminated
airbag deployed with excessive force
airbag did not deploy
injuries sustained from airbag deployment
concussions
bruises
and chest injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall Delays and Inconvenience
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delays and lack of communication from the manufacturer and dealerships regarding the Takata airbag recall can cause inconvenience, anxiety, and a sense of uncertainty for vehicle owners, potentially affecting their safety on the road.
symptoms: No response from dealerships
lack of available parts
delayed repairs
inability to use the passenger seat
and feelings of frustration and concern.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, compromising the safety of the vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Brake pedal felt soft or spongy
brake pedal did not return to its normal position
vehicle crashed into another vehicle
airbag deployed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust and corrosion on the body of the vehicle can lead to structural weakening, compromising the safety of the occupants and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Rust spots or holes on the body
particularly under the rear door
on the rear frame
and on the roof and hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of the paint can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the safety of the occupants and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Paint peeling
flaking
or disintegrating on the roof and hood
exposing the underlying metal to the elements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window door moldings can cause the window to become loose, creating noise and potentially compromising the safety of the occupants.
symptoms: Brittle and disintegrating rubber window door moldings
causing the window to become loose and noisy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic computer box can cause the hatchback to fail to open, potentially stranding the occupants.
symptoms: The hatchback fails to open
and the electronic computer box needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration when braking can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, which can be fatal.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake pedal feels stiff or hard
the engine revs up
and the vehicle may lunge forward or continue moving despite braking efforts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete braking can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly.
symptoms: The vehicle does not stop completely
continues to move for a short distance after braking
or slows down unexpectedly
which can lead to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, which can be fatal.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes lock up
or the vehicle experiences unexpected acceleration or deceleration
which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
